  "course_description": "This course is designed to endow you with an entrepreneurial perspective, enhance your ability to use functional knowledge in an applied setting, and familiarize you with the skills and resources necessary for starting a new venture. By the end of the class you will be able to: -Identify trends and opportunities in the marketplace - Formulate new venture ideas - Analyze your market and validate your customer base - Present a competitive analysis of a specific industry - Create a revenue model, forecast costs and demand, and assess potential profitability - Understand how financing, venture capital and valuation work - Utilize a business model canvas - Put together and present a business plan and pitch - Analyze ventures, both inside and outside of corporations",
